  - {fileID: 1011306259}
  hintDatabase:
  - hintText: Damn rust is eating through the metal. First, give the jammed joint
      a heavy strike to break the crust. Second, yank out the bent nail. Finally,
      bolt the new piece down tight
    correctItemOrder:
    - {fileID: 11400000, guid: 32c870342e36eec46b4e0d67951d4898, type: 2}
    - {fileID: 11400000, guid: 4fef94c1cf37dc240a383205496e3b7d, type: 2}
    - {fileID: 11400000, guid: 7cc11d516f3638e46b130f6587ee0d61, type: 2}
  - hintText: 'Regular maintenance protocol: Unbolt the main pressure valve to release
      the steam. Knock the alignment gear back into place. Pinch the rubber seal
      shut so it doesn''t leak out.'
    correctItemOrder:
    - {fileID: 11400000, guid: 7cc11d516f3638e46b130f6587ee0d61, type: 2}
    - {fileID: 11400000, guid: 32c870342e36eec46b4e0d67951d4898, type: 2}
    - {fileID: 11400000, guid: 4fef94c1cf37dc240a383205496e3b7d, type: 2}
  - hintText: 'To swap the old engine rotor: Snip the rusted safety wire first. Then,
      loosen the mounting nuts. If the casing refuses to open, smash it with everything
      you''ve got.'
    correctItemOrder:
    - {fileID: 11400000, guid: 4fef94c1cf37dc240a383205496e3b7d, type: 2}
    - {fileID: 11400000, guid: 7cc11d516f3638e46b130f6587ee0d61, type: 2}
